race.comment: Tricky. Kris Lees trained NEWY (6) returned from a spell beaten 3L over 1150m at Beaumont (Newcastle) as the favourite. He missed 1L at Newcastle before the spell and has the blinkers on for the first time. Tough to beat with the race fitness and experience. BORDERFALL (4) resumes for the Archibalds, and he's trialled solidly twice at Warwick Farm. Maps for the run of the race and Collett rides and strikes at 22% with the stable. A bold run is likely. SUN TO ME (8) settled back and didn't do a bad at job at Gosford on debut over this trip. Has an inside gate and is a quick improver. Stablemate TAMPA BAY (10) went well here and then improved again, beaten a nose at Gosford over 1000m. Has her first try at 1200m but can feature at a price with average luck in the run.
